This project aims at providing a free version of the Garamond types,
based on the Designs of the Berner specimen from 1592.

In the end, the fonts shall cover extended latin,
greek and cyrillic scripts in different styles
(regular, italic, bold, bolditalic) and design sizes.
There are also fonts containing initials based on those
found in a 16th century french bible print.
The fonts make heavy use of opentype features for specialities
like small caps or different number styles as well as for imitating renaissance typography.